                        <p class="obra-desc" data-lang="en">A six-year-old is hit by a car while running with a bouquet of flowers towards his mother. It is not the accident that breaks him. It is what comes after — the mother who leaves, the father who fades, the adoption, and thirty years of learning that love does not always come from the people who brought you into the world. Autofiction about identity, childhood grief, and what the body remembers. Set in the Basque Country of the nineties.</p>
