                <p class="obra-desc" data-lang="en">Every step was legal. Every document was signed. Every channel received what it was supposed to receive. And at the end of the chain, seventy children slept in their coats. An anatomy of institutional silence in international aid, told by someone who learned to read silences long before.</p>
